+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CAm96bEGwQfKv2ZTr8RUVB","type":"tool_result","content":"-- Multi-tenant analytics dashboard schema\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  email TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  password_hash TEXT NOT NULL,\n  tenant_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  role TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'viewer' CHECK(role IN ('admin', 'viewer', 'editor')),\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS events (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  tenant_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  properties TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  timestamp TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  user_id TEXT,\n  session_id TEXT\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS dashboards (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  tenant_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  owner_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  config TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  FOREIGN KEY (owner_id) REFERENCES users(id)\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS widgets (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  dashboard_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK(type IN ('counter', 'timeseries', 'breakdown', 'funnel')),\n  config TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  position_x INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  position_y INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  width INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n  height INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n  FOREIGN KEY (dashboard_id) REFERENCES dashboards(id) ON DELETE CASCADE\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_events_tenant ON events(tenant_id);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_events_name ON events(name);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_events_timestamp ON events(timestamp);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_dashboards_tenant ON dashboards(tenant_id);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_users_tenant ON users(tenant_id);","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c715d9ad-2e1e-4c30-97e1-cd6749dfa129","uuid":"0b0ecc53-f49e-4f80-9767-2489f41d8b20","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"-- Multi-tenant analytics dashboard schema\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  email TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  password_hash TEXT NOT NULL,\n  tenant_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  role TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'viewer' CHECK(role IN ('admin', 'viewer', 'editor')),\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS events (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  tenant_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  properties TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  timestamp TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  user_id TEXT,\n  session_id TEXT\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS dashboards (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  tenant_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  owner_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  config TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  FOREIGN KEY (owner_id) REFERENCES users(id)\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS widgets (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  dashboard_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK(type IN ('counter', 'timeseries', 'breakdown', 'funnel')),\n  config TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  position_x INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  position_y INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  width INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n  height INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n  FOREIGN KEY (dashboard_id) REFERENCES dashboards(id) ON DELETE CASCADE\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_events_tenant ON events(tenant_id);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_events_name ON events(name);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_events_timestamp ON events(timestamp);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_dashboards_tenant ON dashboards(tenant_id);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_users_tenant ON users(tenant_id);","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VZeYjhnbyswYKXgmSrFDDN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WfbBLCsvuhuJyYaQNwcKvK","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-analytics-dashboard.md","content":"# Analytics Dashboard Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a multi-tenant analytics dashboard REST API in TypeScript with user management, event ingestion, query engine, dashboard CRUD, and data export.\n\n**Architecture:** Layered Express app with route handlers, auth middleware, and a direct SQLite access layer (better-sqlite3). Each feature area gets its own router file; shared middleware handles JWT auth and tenant scoping. The `createApp` factory function wires everything together and is exported for testing.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict), Express 4, better-sqlite3, jsonwebtoken, uuid, Node16 modules\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Project Scaffold — DB module and app factory\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/db.ts`\n- Create: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Create the database module**\n\n```typescript\n// src/db.ts\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\n\nlet _db: Database.Database | null = null;\n\nexport function getDb(dbPath = ':memory:'): Database.Database {\n  if (_db) return _db;\n  _db = new Database(dbPath);\n  _db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  _db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n  const schema = fs.readFileSync(path.join(process.cwd(), 'schema.sql'), 'utf-8');\n  _db.exec(schema);\n  return _db;\n}\n\nexport function resetDb(): void {\n  if (_db) {\n    _db.close();\n    _db = null;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create the minimal app factory**\n\n```typescript\n// src/app.ts\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { getDb } from './db.js';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport function createApp(db?: Database.Database): express.Application {\n  const app = express();\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  const database = db ?? getDb();\n\n  // Attach db to request for use in routes\n  app.use((req, _res, next) => {\n    (req as any).db = database;\n    next();\n  });\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Create index.ts that re-exports createApp**\n\n```typescript\n// src/index.ts\nexport { createApp } from './app.js';\n```\n\n**Step 4: Build to verify**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build\n```\nExpected: no errors\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/db.ts src/app.ts src/index.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: scaffold app factory and db module\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Auth Middleware and Types\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `src/middleware/auth.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Define shared types**\n\n```typescript\n// src/types.ts\nimport { Request } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport interface UserRow {\n  id: string;\n  email: string;\n  password_hash: string;\n  tenant_id: string;\n  role: 'admin' | 'editor' | 'viewer';\n  created_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface EventRow {\n  id: string;\n  tenant_id: string;\n  name: string;\n  properties: string; // JSON string\n  timestamp: string;\n  user_id: string | null;\n  session_id: string | null;\n}\n\nexport interface DashboardRow {\n  id: string;\n  tenant_id: string;\n  name: string;\n  owner_id: string;\n  config: string; // JSON string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface WidgetRow {\n  id: string;\n  dashboard_id: string;\n  type: 'counter' | 'timeseries' | 'breakdown' | 'funnel';\n  config: string; // JSON string\n  position_x: number;\n  position_y: number;\n  width: number;\n  height: number;\n}\n\nexport interface AuthRequest extends Request {\n  user?: UserRow;\n  db: Database.Database;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create auth middleware**\n\n```typescript\n// src/middleware/auth.ts\nimport { Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\nimport jwt from 'jsonwebtoken';\nimport { AuthRequest, UserRow } from '../types.js';\n\nexport const JWT_SECRET = process.env.JWT_SECRET ?? 'dev-secret-change-in-production';\n\nexport function requireAuth(req: AuthRequest, res: Response, next: NextFunction): void {\n  const authHeader = req.headers.authorization;\n  if (!authHeader?.startsWith('Bearer ')) {\n    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const token = authHeader.slice(7);\n  try {\n    const payload = jwt.verify(token, JWT_SECRET) as { userId: string; tenantId: string; role: string };\n    const user = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?').get(payload.userId) as UserRow | undefined;\n    if (!user) {\n      res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });\n      return;\n    }\n    req.user = user;\n    next();\n  } catch {\n    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });\n  }\n}\n\nexport function requireRole(...roles: string[]) {\n  return (req: AuthRequest, res: Response, next: NextFunction): void => {\n    if (!req.user || !roles.includes(req.user.role)) {\n      res.status(403).json({ error: 'Forbidden' });\n      return;\n    }\n    next();\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/types.ts src/middleware/auth.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add auth types and JWT middleware\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: User Management Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/users.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Create user routes**\n\n```typescript\n// src/routes/users.ts\nimport { Router, Response } from 'express';\nimport bcrypt from 'bcryptjs';\nimport jwt from 'jsonwebtoken';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport { AuthRequest, UserRow } from '../types.js';\nimport { requireAuth, requireRole, JWT_SECRET } from '../middleware/auth.js';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\n// POST /api/users/register\nrouter.post('/register', (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { email, password, tenantId, role = 'viewer' } = req.body as {\n    email?: string; password?: string; tenantId?: string; role?: string;\n  };\n  if (!email || !password || !tenantId) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'email, password, tenantId required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const validRoles = ['admin', 'editor', 'viewer'];\n  if (!validRoles.includes(role)) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid role' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const existing = req.db.prepare('SELECT id FROM users WHERE email = ?').get(email);\n  if (existing) {\n    res.status(409).json({ error: 'Email already registered' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const id = uuidv4();\n  const password_hash = bcrypt.hashSync(password, 10);\n  req.db.prepare(\n    'INSERT INTO users (id, email, password_hash, tenant_id, role) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n  ).run(id, email, password_hash, tenantId, role);\n  const token = jwt.sign({ userId: id, tenantId, role }, JWT_SECRET, { expiresIn: '24h' });\n  res.status(201).json({ id, email, tenantId, role, token });\n});\n\n// POST /api/users/login\nrouter.post('/login', (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { email, password } = req.body as { email?: string; password?: string };\n  if (!email || !password) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'email and password required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const user = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?').get(email) as UserRow | undefined;\n  if (!user || !bcrypt.compareSync(password, user.password_hash)) {\n    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid credentials' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const token = jwt.sign({ userId: user.id, tenantId: user.tenant_id, role: user.role }, JWT_SECRET, { expiresIn: '24h' });\n  res.json({ id: user.id, email: user.email, tenantId: user.tenant_id, role: user.role, token });\n});\n\n// GET /api/users/me\nrouter.get('/me', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const user = req.user!;\n  res.json({ id: user.id, email: user.email, tenantId: user.tenant_id, role: user.role, createdAt: user.created_at });\n});\n\n// PATCH /api/users/:userId/role — admin only\nrouter.patch('/:userId/role', requireAuth, requireRole('admin'), (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { userId } = req.params;\n  const { role } = req.body as { role?: string };\n  const validRoles = ['admin', 'editor', 'viewer'];\n  if (!role || !validRoles.includes(role)) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid role' });\n    return;\n  }\n  // Admins can only change users within their tenant\n  const target = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(userId, req.user!.tenant_id) as UserRow | undefined;\n  if (!target) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  req.db.prepare('UPDATE users SET role = ? WHERE id = ?').run(role, userId);\n  res.json({ id: userId, role });\n});\n\nexport default router;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Wire users router into app.ts**\n\n```typescript\n// In createApp, after middleware setup:\nimport usersRouter from './routes/users.js';\n// ...\napp.use('/api/users', usersRouter);\n```\n\nNote: bcryptjs needs to be installed. Check package.json — if not present, use a simple hash or note it. Actually check first.\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/users.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add user registration, login, profile, role management\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Event Ingestion Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/events.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Create events ingestion router**\n\n```typescript\n// src/routes/events.ts\nimport { Router, Response } from 'express';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport { AuthRequest } from '../types.js';\nimport { requireAuth } from '../middleware/auth.js';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\ninterface EventInput {\n  name?: string;\n  properties?: Record<string, unknown>;\n  timestamp?: string;\n}\n\nfunction insertEvent(req: AuthRequest, event: EventInput): { id: string } | null {\n  if (!event.name) return null;\n  const id = uuidv4();\n  const tenantId = req.user!.tenant_id;\n  const userId = req.user!.id;\n  const properties = JSON.stringify(event.properties ?? {});\n  const timestamp = event.timestamp ?? new Date().toISOString();\n  req.db.prepare(\n    'INSERT INTO events (id, tenant_id, name, properties, timestamp, user_id) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n  ).run(id, tenantId, event.name, properties, timestamp, userId);\n  return { id };\n}\n\n// POST /api/events — single event\nrouter.post('/', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const event = req.body as EventInput;\n  const result = insertEvent(req, event);\n  if (!result) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'event name required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  res.status(201).json(result);\n});\n\n// POST /api/events/batch — multiple events\nrouter.post('/batch', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { events } = req.body as { events?: EventInput[] };\n  if (!Array.isArray(events) || events.length === 0) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'events array required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const insertMany = req.db.transaction((evts: EventInput[]) => {\n    return evts.map(e => insertEvent(req, e)).filter(Boolean);\n  });\n  const results = insertMany(events);\n  res.status(201).json({ inserted: results.length, ids: results.map((r: any) => r.id) });\n});\n\nexport default router;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add to app.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport eventsRouter from './routes/events.js';\n// ...\napp.use('/api/events', eventsRouter);\n```\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/events.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add event ingestion (single and batch)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Query Engine Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/query.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 4\n\n**Step 1: Create query router**\n\n```typescript\n// src/routes/query.ts\nimport { Router, Response } from 'express';\nimport { AuthRequest } from '../types.js';\nimport { requireAuth } from '../middleware/auth.js';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\n// POST /api/query/count\n// Body: { eventName: string, filters?: Record<string, string> }\nrouter.post('/count', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { eventName, filters } = req.body as { eventName?: string; filters?: Record<string, string> };\n  if (!eventName) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'eventName required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const tenantId = req.user!.tenant_id;\n  let sql = 'SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ? AND name = ?';\n  const params: unknown[] = [tenantId, eventName];\n\n  if (filters) {\n    for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(filters)) {\n      sql += ` AND json_extract(properties, '$.${key}') = ?`;\n      params.push(value);\n    }\n  }\n\n  const row = req.db.prepare(sql).get(...params as [unknown, ...unknown[]]) as { count: number };\n  res.json({ count: row.count });\n});\n\n// POST /api/query/timeseries\n// Body: { eventName: string, interval: 'hour'|'day'|'week'|'month', startDate?: string, endDate?: string }\nrouter.post('/timeseries', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { eventName, interval = 'day', startDate, endDate } = req.body as {\n    eventName?: string; interval?: string; startDate?: string; endDate?: string;\n  };\n  if (!eventName) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'eventName required' });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const formatMap: Record<string, string> = {\n    hour: '%Y-%m-%d %H:00',\n    day: '%Y-%m-%d',\n    week: '%Y-%W',\n    month: '%Y-%m',\n  };\n  const fmt = formatMap[interval] ?? '%Y-%m-%d';\n  const tenantId = req.user!.tenant_id;\n  const params: unknown[] = [tenantId, eventName];\n  let sql = `SELECT strftime('${fmt}', timestamp) as bucket, COUNT(*) as count\n             FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ? AND name = ?`;\n  if (startDate) { sql += ' AND timestamp >= ?'; params.push(startDate); }\n  if (endDate) { sql += ' AND timestamp <= ?'; params.push(endDate); }\n  sql += ' GROUP BY bucket ORDER BY bucket';\n\n  const rows = req.db.prepare(sql).all(...params as [unknown, ...unknown[]]) as { bucket: string; count: number }[];\n  res.json({ data: rows });\n});\n\n// POST /api/query/breakdown\n// Body: { eventName: string, property: string, filters?: Record<string, string> }\nrouter.post('/breakdown', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { eventName, property, filters } = req.body as {\n    eventName?: string; property?: string; filters?: Record<string, string>;\n  };\n  if (!eventName || !property) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'eventName and property required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const tenantId = req.user!.tenant_id;\n  const params: unknown[] = [tenantId, eventName];\n  let sql = `SELECT json_extract(properties, '$.${property}') as value, COUNT(*) as count\n             FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ? AND name = ?`;\n  if (filters) {\n    for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(filters)) {\n      sql += ` AND json_extract(properties, '$.${key}') = ?`;\n      params.push(value);\n    }\n  }\n  sql += ' GROUP BY value ORDER BY count DESC';\n\n  const rows = req.db.prepare(sql).all(...params as [unknown, ...unknown[]]) as { value: string; count: number }[];\n  res.json({ data: rows });\n});\n\nexport default router;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add to app.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport queryRouter from './routes/query.js';\n// ...\napp.use('/api/query', queryRouter);\n```\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/query.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add query engine (count, timeseries, breakdown)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Dashboard CRUD Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/dashboards.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Create dashboards router**\n\n```typescript\n// src/routes/dashboards.ts\nimport { Router, Response } from 'express';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport { AuthRequest, DashboardRow, WidgetRow } from '../types.js';\nimport { requireAuth } from '../middleware/auth.js';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\n// GET /api/dashboards\nrouter.get('/', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const rows = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE tenant_id = ? ORDER BY created_at DESC')\n    .all(req.user!.tenant_id) as DashboardRow[];\n  res.json(rows.map(d => ({ ...d, config: JSON.parse(d.config) })));\n});\n\n// POST /api/dashboards\nrouter.post('/', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { name, config = {} } = req.body as { name?: string; config?: Record<string, unknown> };\n  if (!name) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'name required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const id = uuidv4();\n  const now = new Date().toISOString();\n  req.db.prepare(\n    'INSERT INTO dashboards (id, tenant_id, name, owner_id, config, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n  ).run(id, req.user!.tenant_id, name, req.user!.id, JSON.stringify(config), now, now);\n  res.status(201).json({ id, name, tenantId: req.user!.tenant_id, config, createdAt: now, updatedAt: now });\n});\n\n// GET /api/dashboards/:id\nrouter.get('/:id', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const dashboard = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(req.params.id, req.user!.tenant_id) as DashboardRow | undefined;\n  if (!dashboard) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const widgets = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM widgets WHERE dashboard_id = ?')\n    .all(dashboard.id) as WidgetRow[];\n  res.json({\n    ...dashboard,\n    config: JSON.parse(dashboard.config),\n    widgets: widgets.map(w => ({ ...w, config: JSON.parse(w.config) })),\n  });\n});\n\n// PATCH /api/dashboards/:id\nrouter.patch('/:id', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const dashboard = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(req.params.id, req.user!.tenant_id) as DashboardRow | undefined;\n  if (!dashboard) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const { name, config } = req.body as { name?: string; config?: Record<string, unknown> };\n  const newName = name ?? dashboard.name;\n  const newConfig = config !== undefined ? JSON.stringify(config) : dashboard.config;\n  const now = new Date().toISOString();\n  req.db.prepare('UPDATE dashboards SET name = ?, config = ?, updated_at = ? WHERE id = ?')\n    .run(newName, newConfig, now, dashboard.id);\n  res.json({ id: dashboard.id, name: newName, config: JSON.parse(newConfig), updatedAt: now });\n});\n\n// DELETE /api/dashboards/:id\nrouter.delete('/:id', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const dashboard = req.db.prepare('SELECT id FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(req.params.id, req.user!.tenant_id);\n  if (!dashboard) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  req.db.prepare('DELETE FROM dashboards WHERE id = ?').run(req.params.id);\n  res.status(204).send();\n});\n\n// POST /api/dashboards/:id/widgets\nrouter.post('/:id/widgets', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const dashboard = req.db.prepare('SELECT id FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(req.params.id, req.user!.tenant_id);\n  if (!dashboard) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const { type, config = {}, position_x = 0, position_y = 0, width = 1, height = 1 } = req.body as {\n    type?: string; config?: Record<string, unknown>; position_x?: number; position_y?: number; width?: number; height?: number;\n  };\n  const validTypes = ['counter', 'timeseries', 'breakdown', 'funnel'];\n  if (!type || !validTypes.includes(type)) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'valid type required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const id = uuidv4();\n  req.db.prepare(\n    'INSERT INTO widgets (id, dashboard_id, type, config, position_x, position_y, width, height) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n  ).run(id, req.params.id, type, JSON.stringify(config), position_x, position_y, width, height);\n  res.status(201).json({ id, dashboardId: req.params.id, type, config, position_x, position_y, width, height });\n});\n\nexport default router;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add to app.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport dashboardsRouter from './routes/dashboards.js';\n// ...\napp.use('/api/dashboards', dashboardsRouter);\n```\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/dashboards.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add dashboard CRUD and widget management\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Data Export Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/export.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 4, Task 6\n\n**Step 1: Create export router**\n\n```typescript\n// src/routes/export.ts\nimport { Router, Response } from 'express';\nimport { AuthRequest, EventRow, DashboardRow, WidgetRow } from '../types.js';\nimport { requireAuth } from '../middleware/auth.js';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\nfunction toCSV(rows: Record<string, unknown>[]): string {\n  if (rows.length === 0) return '';\n  const headers = Object.keys(rows[0]);\n  const lines = [headers.join(',')];\n  for (const row of rows) {\n    lines.push(headers.map(h => {\n      const v = row[h];\n      const str = v === null || v === undefined ? '' : String(v);\n      return str.includes(',') || str.includes('\"') || str.includes('\\n')\n        ? `\"${str.replace(/\"/g, '\"\"')}\"` : str;\n    }).join(','));\n  }\n  return lines.join('\\n');\n}\n\n// GET /api/export/events?format=json|csv\nrouter.get('/events', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const format = (req.query.format as string) ?? 'json';\n  const tenantId = req.user!.tenant_id;\n  const rows = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ? ORDER BY timestamp DESC')\n    .all(tenantId) as EventRow[];\n\n  const data = rows.map(r => ({ ...r, properties: JSON.parse(r.properties) }));\n\n  if (format === 'csv') {\n    const flatRows = rows.map(r => ({ ...r }));\n    res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/csv');\n    res.setHeader('Content-Disposition', 'attachment; filename=\"events.csv\"');\n    res.send(toCSV(flatRows as Record<string, unknown>[]));\n    return;\n  }\n  res.json(data);\n});\n\n// GET /api/export/dashboards/:id?format=json|csv\nrouter.get('/dashboards/:id', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const format = (req.query.format as string) ?? 'json';\n  const dashboard = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(req.params.id, req.user!.tenant_id) as DashboardRow | undefined;\n  if (!dashboard) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const widgets = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM widgets WHERE dashboard_id = ?')\n    .all(dashboard.id) as WidgetRow[];\n\n  if (format === 'csv') {\n    res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/csv');\n    res.setHeader('Content-Disposition', `attachment; filename=\"dashboard-${dashboard.id}.csv\"`);\n    res.send(toCSV(widgets as unknown as Record<string, unknown>[]));\n    return;\n  }\n  res.json({\n    ...dashboard,\n    config: JSON.parse(dashboard.config),\n    widgets: widgets.map(w => ({ ...w, config: JSON.parse(w.config) })),\n  });\n});\n\nexport default router;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add to app.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport exportRouter from './routes/export.js';\n// ...\napp.use('/api/export', exportRouter);\n```\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/export.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add data export (events and dashboards, JSON and CSV)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Final app.ts Assembly + Build + Lint Pass\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/app.ts` — finalize all imports and router wiring\n\n**Dependencies:** Tasks 1-7\n\n**Step 1: Write final app.ts**\n\n```typescript\n// src/app.ts\nimport express from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { getDb } from './db.js';\nimport usersRouter from './routes/users.js';\nimport eventsRouter from './routes/events.js';\nimport queryRouter from './routes/query.js';\nimport dashboardsRouter from './routes/dashboards.js';\nimport exportRouter from './routes/export.js';\n\nexport function createApp(db?: Database.Database): express.Application {\n  const app = express();\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  const database = db ?? getDb();\n\n  app.use((req, _res, next) => {\n    (req as any).db = database;\n    next();\n  });\n\n  app.use('/api/users', usersRouter);\n  app.use('/api/events', eventsRouter);\n  app.use('/api/query', queryRouter);\n  app.use('/api/dashboards', dashboardsRouter);\n  app.use('/api/export', exportRouter);\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run full build and lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build && npm run lint\n```\nExpected: 0 errors, 0 warnings\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A\ngit commit -m \"feat: assemble final app with all routes\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Write Integration Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/tests/app.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 8\n\n**Step 1: Write tests covering all major features**\n\nCover: register, login, auth protection (401), event ingestion, batch, count query, timeseries, breakdown, dashboard CRUD, export JSON, export CSV, tenant isolation.\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/app.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../app.js';\nimport { getDb, resetDb } from '../db.js';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nlet db: Database.Database;\nlet app: ReturnType<typeof createApp>;\n\nbeforeEach(() => {\n  resetDb();\n  db = getDb(':memory:');\n  app = createApp(db);\n});\n\nafterEach(() => {\n  resetDb();\n});\n\nasync function registerAndLogin(email: string, tenantId: string, role = 'admin') {\n  const reg = await request(app)\n    .post('/api/users/register')\n    .send({ email, password: 'password123', tenantId, role });\n  return reg.body.token as string;\n}\n\ndescribe('User Management', () => {\n  it('registers a new user', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/users/register')\n      .send({ email: 'a@test.com', password: 'pass', tenantId: 'tenant1' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.token).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('returns 409 for duplicate email', async () => {\n    await request(app).post('/api/users/register').send({ email: 'a@test.com', password: 'p', tenantId: 't1' });\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/users/register').send({ email: 'a@test.com', password: 'p', tenantId: 't1' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(409);\n  });\n\n  it('logs in with correct credentials', async () => {\n    await request(app).post('/api/users/register').send({ email: 'b@test.com', password: 'pass', tenantId: 't1' });\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/users/login').send({ email: 'b@test.com', password: 'pass' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.token).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 for wrong password', async () => {\n    await request(app).post('/api/users/register').send({ email: 'c@test.com', password: 'pass', tenantId: 't1' });\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/users/login').send({ email: 'c@test.com', password: 'wrong' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 for unauthenticated /me', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/users/me');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n\n  it('returns user profile', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('d@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/users/me').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.email).toBe('d@test.com');\n  });\n\n  it('admin can change role of user in same tenant', async () => {\n    const adminToken = await registerAndLogin('admin@t.com', 'tenant1', 'admin');\n    const viewerReg = await request(app).post('/api/users/register')\n      .send({ email: 'viewer@t.com', password: 'pass', tenantId: 'tenant1', role: 'viewer' });\n    const viewerId = viewerReg.body.id;\n    const res = await request(app).patch(`/api/users/${viewerId}/role`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${adminToken}`)\n      .send({ role: 'editor' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.role).toBe('editor');\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Event Ingestion', () => {\n  it('ingests a single event', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('e@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/events')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' } });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.id).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 without auth', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/events').send({ name: 'test' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n\n  it('ingests batch events', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('f@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/events/batch')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ events: [{ name: 'click' }, { name: 'click' }, { name: 'view' }] });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.inserted).toBe(3);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Query Engine', () => {\n  async function setupData(token: string) {\n    await request(app).post('/api/events/batch')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ events: [\n        { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' } },\n        { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/about' } },\n        { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' } },\n        { name: 'click' },\n      ]});\n  }\n\n  it('counts events by name', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('g@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    await setupData(token);\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/query/count')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ eventName: 'page_view' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.count).toBe(3);\n  });\n\n  it('returns timeseries data', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('h@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    await setupData(token);\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/query/timeseries')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ eventName: 'page_view', interval: 'day' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(Array.isArray(res.body.data)).toBe(true);\n  });\n\n  it('returns breakdown data', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('i@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    await setupData(token);\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/query/breakdown')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ eventName: 'page_view', property: 'url' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.data.find((d: any) => d.value === '/home')?.count).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('enforces tenant isolation', async () => {\n    const t1 = await registerAndLogin('t1@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const t2 = await registerAndLogin('t2@test.com', 'tenant2');\n    await request(app).post('/api/events').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t1}`).send({ name: 'page_view' });\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/query/count')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t2}`)\n      .send({ eventName: 'page_view' });\n    expect(res.body.count).toBe(0);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Dashboard CRUD', () => {\n  it('creates a dashboard', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('j@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/dashboards')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'My Dashboard' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.id).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('lists dashboards for tenant', async () => {\n    const t1 = await registerAndLogin('k1@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const t2 = await registerAndLogin('k2@test.com', 'tenant2');\n    await request(app).post('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t1}`).send({ name: 'D1' });\n    await request(app).post('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t2}`).send({ name: 'D2' });\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t1}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(res.body[0].name).toBe('D1');\n  });\n\n  it('updates a dashboard', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('l@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const create = await request(app).post('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`).send({ name: 'Old' });\n    const res = await request(app).patch(`/api/dashboards/${create.body.id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'New' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.name).toBe('New');\n  });\n\n  it('deletes a dashboard', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('m@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const create = await request(app).post('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`).send({ name: 'Del' });\n    const res = await request(app).delete(`/api/dashboards/${create.body.id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(204);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Data Export', () => {\n  it('exports events as JSON', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('n@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    await request(app).post('/api/events').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`).send({ name: 'test' });\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/export/events').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(Array.isArray(res.body)).toBe(true);\n    expect(res.body[0].name).toBe('test');\n  });\n\n  it('exports events as CSV', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('o@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    await request(app).post('/api/events').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`).send({ name: 'test' });\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/export/events?format=csv').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.headers['content-type']).toContain('text/csv');\n    expect(res.text).toContain('id,tenant_id');\n  });\n\n  it('exports dashboard as JSON', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('p@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const dash = await request(app).post('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`).send({ name: 'Exp' });\n    const res = await request(app).get(`/api/export/dashboards/${dash.body.id}`).set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.name).toBe('Exp');\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 for unauthenticated export', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/export/events');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\nExpected: all pass\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/tests/\ngit commit -m \"test: add integration tests for all API features\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Final Verification\n\n**Dependencies:** Tasks 1-9\n\n**Step 1: Full build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\nExpected: 0 errors\n\n**Step 2: Lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint\n```\nExpected: 0 errors\n\n**Step 3: Tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\nExpected: all pass\n\n**Step 4: Review diff**\n\n```bash\ngit diff HEAD~10\n```\n\n**Step 5: Final commit if needed**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"chore: analytics dashboard implementation complete\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- `bcryptjs` is not in package.json — use Node's built-in `crypto` for password hashing (scrypt or pbkdf2) OR check if `bcrypt` is available. Actually, use `crypto.scryptSync` from Node stdlib to avoid adding dependencies.\n- All routes that return tenant data must filter by `req.user!.tenant_id`\n- The `(req as any).db` pattern is necessary because Express's `Request` type doesn't have `db`; the `AuthRequest` interface solves this for authenticated routes\n- SQLite's `json_extract` function is used for property-based filtering in queries\n- The `resetDb()` function is critical for test isolation — call it in `afterEach`\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":725,"cache_read_input_tokens":25953,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":725},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c715d9ad-2e1e-4c30-97e1-cd6749dfa129","uuid":"e61f002a-3c3e-4a44-85f4-f2356f23e927"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WfbBLCsvuhuJyYaQNwcKvK","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-analytics-dashboard.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c715d9ad-2e1e-4c30-97e1-cd6749dfa129","uuid":"a568c392-aa0c-43f2-9e34-8ac05747ae73","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-analytics-dashboard.md","content":"# Analytics Dashboard Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a multi-tenant analytics dashboard REST API in TypeScript with user management, event ingestion, query engine, dashboard CRUD, and data export.\n\n**Architecture:** Layered Express app with route handlers, auth middleware, and a direct SQLite access layer (better-sqlite3). Each feature area gets its own router file; shared middleware handles JWT auth and tenant scoping. The `createApp` factory function wires everything together and is exported for testing.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict), Express 4, better-sqlite3, jsonwebtoken, uuid, Node16 modules\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Project Scaffold — DB module and app factory\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/db.ts`\n- Create: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Create the database module**\n\n```typescript\n// src/db.ts\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\n\nlet _db: Database.Database | null = null;\n\nexport function getDb(dbPath = ':memory:'): Database.Database {\n  if (_db) return _db;\n  _db = new Database(dbPath);\n  _db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  _db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n  const schema = fs.readFileSync(path.join(process.cwd(), 'schema.sql'), 'utf-8');\n  _db.exec(schema);\n  return _db;\n}\n\nexport function resetDb(): void {\n  if (_db) {\n    _db.close();\n    _db = null;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create the minimal app factory**\n\n```typescript\n// src/app.ts\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { getDb } from './db.js';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport function createApp(db?: Database.Database): express.Application {\n  const app = express();\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  const database = db ?? getDb();\n\n  // Attach db to request for use in routes\n  app.use((req, _res, next) => {\n    (req as any).db = database;\n    next();\n  });\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Create index.ts that re-exports createApp**\n\n```typescript\n// src/index.ts\nexport { createApp } from './app.js';\n```\n\n**Step 4: Build to verify**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build\n```\nExpected: no errors\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/db.ts src/app.ts src/index.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: scaffold app factory and db module\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Auth Middleware and Types\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `src/middleware/auth.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Define shared types**\n\n```typescript\n// src/types.ts\nimport { Request } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport interface UserRow {\n  id: string;\n  email: string;\n  password_hash: string;\n  tenant_id: string;\n  role: 'admin' | 'editor' | 'viewer';\n  created_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface EventRow {\n  id: string;\n  tenant_id: string;\n  name: string;\n  properties: string; // JSON string\n  timestamp: string;\n  user_id: string | null;\n  session_id: string | null;\n}\n\nexport interface DashboardRow {\n  id: string;\n  tenant_id: string;\n  name: string;\n  owner_id: string;\n  config: string; // JSON string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface WidgetRow {\n  id: string;\n  dashboard_id: string;\n  type: 'counter' | 'timeseries' | 'breakdown' | 'funnel';\n  config: string; // JSON string\n  position_x: number;\n  position_y: number;\n  width: number;\n  height: number;\n}\n\nexport interface AuthRequest extends Request {\n  user?: UserRow;\n  db: Database.Database;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create auth middleware**\n\n```typescript\n// src/middleware/auth.ts\nimport { Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\nimport jwt from 'jsonwebtoken';\nimport { AuthRequest, UserRow } from '../types.js';\n\nexport const JWT_SECRET = process.env.JWT_SECRET ?? 'dev-secret-change-in-production';\n\nexport function requireAuth(req: AuthRequest, res: Response, next: NextFunction): void {\n  const authHeader = req.headers.authorization;\n  if (!authHeader?.startsWith('Bearer ')) {\n    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const token = authHeader.slice(7);\n  try {\n    const payload = jwt.verify(token, JWT_SECRET) as { userId: string; tenantId: string; role: string };\n    const user = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?').get(payload.userId) as UserRow | undefined;\n    if (!user) {\n      res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });\n      return;\n    }\n    req.user = user;\n    next();\n  } catch {\n    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });\n  }\n}\n\nexport function requireRole(...roles: string[]) {\n  return (req: AuthRequest, res: Response, next: NextFunction): void => {\n    if (!req.user || !roles.includes(req.user.role)) {\n      res.status(403).json({ error: 'Forbidden' });\n      return;\n    }\n    next();\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/types.ts src/middleware/auth.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add auth types and JWT middleware\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: User Management Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/users.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Create user routes**\n\n```typescript\n// src/routes/users.ts\nimport { Router, Response } from 'express';\nimport bcrypt from 'bcryptjs';\nimport jwt from 'jsonwebtoken';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport { AuthRequest, UserRow } from '../types.js';\nimport { requireAuth, requireRole, JWT_SECRET } from '../middleware/auth.js';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\n// POST /api/users/register\nrouter.post('/register', (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { email, password, tenantId, role = 'viewer' } = req.body as {\n    email?: string; password?: string; tenantId?: string; role?: string;\n  };\n  if (!email || !password || !tenantId) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'email, password, tenantId required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const validRoles = ['admin', 'editor', 'viewer'];\n  if (!validRoles.includes(role)) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid role' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const existing = req.db.prepare('SELECT id FROM users WHERE email = ?').get(email);\n  if (existing) {\n    res.status(409).json({ error: 'Email already registered' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const id = uuidv4();\n  const password_hash = bcrypt.hashSync(password, 10);\n  req.db.prepare(\n    'INSERT INTO users (id, email, password_hash, tenant_id, role) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n  ).run(id, email, password_hash, tenantId, role);\n  const token = jwt.sign({ userId: id, tenantId, role }, JWT_SECRET, { expiresIn: '24h' });\n  res.status(201).json({ id, email, tenantId, role, token });\n});\n\n// POST /api/users/login\nrouter.post('/login', (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { email, password } = req.body as { email?: string; password?: string };\n  if (!email || !password) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'email and password required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const user = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?').get(email) as UserRow | undefined;\n  if (!user || !bcrypt.compareSync(password, user.password_hash)) {\n    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid credentials' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const token = jwt.sign({ userId: user.id, tenantId: user.tenant_id, role: user.role }, JWT_SECRET, { expiresIn: '24h' });\n  res.json({ id: user.id, email: user.email, tenantId: user.tenant_id, role: user.role, token });\n});\n\n// GET /api/users/me\nrouter.get('/me', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const user = req.user!;\n  res.json({ id: user.id, email: user.email, tenantId: user.tenant_id, role: user.role, createdAt: user.created_at });\n});\n\n// PATCH /api/users/:userId/role — admin only\nrouter.patch('/:userId/role', requireAuth, requireRole('admin'), (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { userId } = req.params;\n  const { role } = req.body as { role?: string };\n  const validRoles = ['admin', 'editor', 'viewer'];\n  if (!role || !validRoles.includes(role)) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid role' });\n    return;\n  }\n  // Admins can only change users within their tenant\n  const target = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(userId, req.user!.tenant_id) as UserRow | undefined;\n  if (!target) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  req.db.prepare('UPDATE users SET role = ? WHERE id = ?').run(role, userId);\n  res.json({ id: userId, role });\n});\n\nexport default router;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Wire users router into app.ts**\n\n```typescript\n// In createApp, after middleware setup:\nimport usersRouter from './routes/users.js';\n// ...\napp.use('/api/users', usersRouter);\n```\n\nNote: bcryptjs needs to be installed. Check package.json — if not present, use a simple hash or note it. Actually check first.\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/users.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add user registration, login, profile, role management\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Event Ingestion Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/events.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Create events ingestion router**\n\n```typescript\n// src/routes/events.ts\nimport { Router, Response } from 'express';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport { AuthRequest } from '../types.js';\nimport { requireAuth } from '../middleware/auth.js';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\ninterface EventInput {\n  name?: string;\n  properties?: Record<string, unknown>;\n  timestamp?: string;\n}\n\nfunction insertEvent(req: AuthRequest, event: EventInput): { id: string } | null {\n  if (!event.name) return null;\n  const id = uuidv4();\n  const tenantId = req.user!.tenant_id;\n  const userId = req.user!.id;\n  const properties = JSON.stringify(event.properties ?? {});\n  const timestamp = event.timestamp ?? new Date().toISOString();\n  req.db.prepare(\n    'INSERT INTO events (id, tenant_id, name, properties, timestamp, user_id) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n  ).run(id, tenantId, event.name, properties, timestamp, userId);\n  return { id };\n}\n\n// POST /api/events — single event\nrouter.post('/', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const event = req.body as EventInput;\n  const result = insertEvent(req, event);\n  if (!result) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'event name required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  res.status(201).json(result);\n});\n\n// POST /api/events/batch — multiple events\nrouter.post('/batch', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { events } = req.body as { events?: EventInput[] };\n  if (!Array.isArray(events) || events.length === 0) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'events array required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const insertMany = req.db.transaction((evts: EventInput[]) => {\n    return evts.map(e => insertEvent(req, e)).filter(Boolean);\n  });\n  const results = insertMany(events);\n  res.status(201).json({ inserted: results.length, ids: results.map((r: any) => r.id) });\n});\n\nexport default router;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add to app.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport eventsRouter from './routes/events.js';\n// ...\napp.use('/api/events', eventsRouter);\n```\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/events.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add event ingestion (single and batch)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Query Engine Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/query.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 4\n\n**Step 1: Create query router**\n\n```typescript\n// src/routes/query.ts\nimport { Router, Response } from 'express';\nimport { AuthRequest } from '../types.js';\nimport { requireAuth } from '../middleware/auth.js';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\n// POST /api/query/count\n// Body: { eventName: string, filters?: Record<string, string> }\nrouter.post('/count', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { eventName, filters } = req.body as { eventName?: string; filters?: Record<string, string> };\n  if (!eventName) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'eventName required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const tenantId = req.user!.tenant_id;\n  let sql = 'SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ? AND name = ?';\n  const params: unknown[] = [tenantId, eventName];\n\n  if (filters) {\n    for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(filters)) {\n      sql += ` AND json_extract(properties, '$.${key}') = ?`;\n      params.push(value);\n    }\n  }\n\n  const row = req.db.prepare(sql).get(...params as [unknown, ...unknown[]]) as { count: number };\n  res.json({ count: row.count });\n});\n\n// POST /api/query/timeseries\n// Body: { eventName: string, interval: 'hour'|'day'|'week'|'month', startDate?: string, endDate?: string }\nrouter.post('/timeseries', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { eventName, interval = 'day', startDate, endDate } = req.body as {\n    eventName?: string; interval?: string; startDate?: string; endDate?: string;\n  };\n  if (!eventName) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'eventName required' });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const formatMap: Record<string, string> = {\n    hour: '%Y-%m-%d %H:00',\n    day: '%Y-%m-%d',\n    week: '%Y-%W',\n    month: '%Y-%m',\n  };\n  const fmt = formatMap[interval] ?? '%Y-%m-%d';\n  const tenantId = req.user!.tenant_id;\n  const params: unknown[] = [tenantId, eventName];\n  let sql = `SELECT strftime('${fmt}', timestamp) as bucket, COUNT(*) as count\n             FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ? AND name = ?`;\n  if (startDate) { sql += ' AND timestamp >= ?'; params.push(startDate); }\n  if (endDate) { sql += ' AND timestamp <= ?'; params.push(endDate); }\n  sql += ' GROUP BY bucket ORDER BY bucket';\n\n  const rows = req.db.prepare(sql).all(...params as [unknown, ...unknown[]]) as { bucket: string; count: number }[];\n  res.json({ data: rows });\n});\n\n// POST /api/query/breakdown\n// Body: { eventName: string, property: string, filters?: Record<string, string> }\nrouter.post('/breakdown', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { eventName, property, filters } = req.body as {\n    eventName?: string; property?: string; filters?: Record<string, string>;\n  };\n  if (!eventName || !property) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'eventName and property required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const tenantId = req.user!.tenant_id;\n  const params: unknown[] = [tenantId, eventName];\n  let sql = `SELECT json_extract(properties, '$.${property}') as value, COUNT(*) as count\n             FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ? AND name = ?`;\n  if (filters) {\n    for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(filters)) {\n      sql += ` AND json_extract(properties, '$.${key}') = ?`;\n      params.push(value);\n    }\n  }\n  sql += ' GROUP BY value ORDER BY count DESC';\n\n  const rows = req.db.prepare(sql).all(...params as [unknown, ...unknown[]]) as { value: string; count: number }[];\n  res.json({ data: rows });\n});\n\nexport default router;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add to app.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport queryRouter from './routes/query.js';\n// ...\napp.use('/api/query', queryRouter);\n```\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/query.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add query engine (count, timeseries, breakdown)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Dashboard CRUD Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/dashboards.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Create dashboards router**\n\n```typescript\n// src/routes/dashboards.ts\nimport { Router, Response } from 'express';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport { AuthRequest, DashboardRow, WidgetRow } from '../types.js';\nimport { requireAuth } from '../middleware/auth.js';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\n// GET /api/dashboards\nrouter.get('/', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const rows = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE tenant_id = ? ORDER BY created_at DESC')\n    .all(req.user!.tenant_id) as DashboardRow[];\n  res.json(rows.map(d => ({ ...d, config: JSON.parse(d.config) })));\n});\n\n// POST /api/dashboards\nrouter.post('/', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const { name, config = {} } = req.body as { name?: string; config?: Record<string, unknown> };\n  if (!name) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'name required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const id = uuidv4();\n  const now = new Date().toISOString();\n  req.db.prepare(\n    'INSERT INTO dashboards (id, tenant_id, name, owner_id, config, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n  ).run(id, req.user!.tenant_id, name, req.user!.id, JSON.stringify(config), now, now);\n  res.status(201).json({ id, name, tenantId: req.user!.tenant_id, config, createdAt: now, updatedAt: now });\n});\n\n// GET /api/dashboards/:id\nrouter.get('/:id', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const dashboard = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(req.params.id, req.user!.tenant_id) as DashboardRow | undefined;\n  if (!dashboard) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const widgets = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM widgets WHERE dashboard_id = ?')\n    .all(dashboard.id) as WidgetRow[];\n  res.json({\n    ...dashboard,\n    config: JSON.parse(dashboard.config),\n    widgets: widgets.map(w => ({ ...w, config: JSON.parse(w.config) })),\n  });\n});\n\n// PATCH /api/dashboards/:id\nrouter.patch('/:id', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const dashboard = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(req.params.id, req.user!.tenant_id) as DashboardRow | undefined;\n  if (!dashboard) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const { name, config } = req.body as { name?: string; config?: Record<string, unknown> };\n  const newName = name ?? dashboard.name;\n  const newConfig = config !== undefined ? JSON.stringify(config) : dashboard.config;\n  const now = new Date().toISOString();\n  req.db.prepare('UPDATE dashboards SET name = ?, config = ?, updated_at = ? WHERE id = ?')\n    .run(newName, newConfig, now, dashboard.id);\n  res.json({ id: dashboard.id, name: newName, config: JSON.parse(newConfig), updatedAt: now });\n});\n\n// DELETE /api/dashboards/:id\nrouter.delete('/:id', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const dashboard = req.db.prepare('SELECT id FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(req.params.id, req.user!.tenant_id);\n  if (!dashboard) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  req.db.prepare('DELETE FROM dashboards WHERE id = ?').run(req.params.id);\n  res.status(204).send();\n});\n\n// POST /api/dashboards/:id/widgets\nrouter.post('/:id/widgets', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const dashboard = req.db.prepare('SELECT id FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(req.params.id, req.user!.tenant_id);\n  if (!dashboard) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const { type, config = {}, position_x = 0, position_y = 0, width = 1, height = 1 } = req.body as {\n    type?: string; config?: Record<string, unknown>; position_x?: number; position_y?: number; width?: number; height?: number;\n  };\n  const validTypes = ['counter', 'timeseries', 'breakdown', 'funnel'];\n  if (!type || !validTypes.includes(type)) {\n    res.status(400).json({ error: 'valid type required' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const id = uuidv4();\n  req.db.prepare(\n    'INSERT INTO widgets (id, dashboard_id, type, config, position_x, position_y, width, height) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n  ).run(id, req.params.id, type, JSON.stringify(config), position_x, position_y, width, height);\n  res.status(201).json({ id, dashboardId: req.params.id, type, config, position_x, position_y, width, height });\n});\n\nexport default router;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add to app.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport dashboardsRouter from './routes/dashboards.js';\n// ...\napp.use('/api/dashboards', dashboardsRouter);\n```\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/dashboards.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add dashboard CRUD and widget management\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Data Export Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/export.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 4, Task 6\n\n**Step 1: Create export router**\n\n```typescript\n// src/routes/export.ts\nimport { Router, Response } from 'express';\nimport { AuthRequest, EventRow, DashboardRow, WidgetRow } from '../types.js';\nimport { requireAuth } from '../middleware/auth.js';\n\nconst router = Router();\n\nfunction toCSV(rows: Record<string, unknown>[]): string {\n  if (rows.length === 0) return '';\n  const headers = Object.keys(rows[0]);\n  const lines = [headers.join(',')];\n  for (const row of rows) {\n    lines.push(headers.map(h => {\n      const v = row[h];\n      const str = v === null || v === undefined ? '' : String(v);\n      return str.includes(',') || str.includes('\"') || str.includes('\\n')\n        ? `\"${str.replace(/\"/g, '\"\"')}\"` : str;\n    }).join(','));\n  }\n  return lines.join('\\n');\n}\n\n// GET /api/export/events?format=json|csv\nrouter.get('/events', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const format = (req.query.format as string) ?? 'json';\n  const tenantId = req.user!.tenant_id;\n  const rows = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ? ORDER BY timestamp DESC')\n    .all(tenantId) as EventRow[];\n\n  const data = rows.map(r => ({ ...r, properties: JSON.parse(r.properties) }));\n\n  if (format === 'csv') {\n    const flatRows = rows.map(r => ({ ...r }));\n    res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/csv');\n    res.setHeader('Content-Disposition', 'attachment; filename=\"events.csv\"');\n    res.send(toCSV(flatRows as Record<string, unknown>[]));\n    return;\n  }\n  res.json(data);\n});\n\n// GET /api/export/dashboards/:id?format=json|csv\nrouter.get('/dashboards/:id', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res: Response): void => {\n  const format = (req.query.format as string) ?? 'json';\n  const dashboard = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n    .get(req.params.id, req.user!.tenant_id) as DashboardRow | undefined;\n  if (!dashboard) {\n    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n    return;\n  }\n  const widgets = req.db.prepare('SELECT * FROM widgets WHERE dashboard_id = ?')\n    .all(dashboard.id) as WidgetRow[];\n\n  if (format === 'csv') {\n    res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/csv');\n    res.setHeader('Content-Disposition', `attachment; filename=\"dashboard-${dashboard.id}.csv\"`);\n    res.send(toCSV(widgets as unknown as Record<string, unknown>[]));\n    return;\n  }\n  res.json({\n    ...dashboard,\n    config: JSON.parse(dashboard.config),\n    widgets: widgets.map(w => ({ ...w, config: JSON.parse(w.config) })),\n  });\n});\n\nexport default router;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add to app.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport exportRouter from './routes/export.js';\n// ...\napp.use('/api/export', exportRouter);\n```\n\n**Step 3: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/export.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add data export (events and dashboards, JSON and CSV)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Final app.ts Assembly + Build + Lint Pass\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/app.ts` — finalize all imports and router wiring\n\n**Dependencies:** Tasks 1-7\n\n**Step 1: Write final app.ts**\n\n```typescript\n// src/app.ts\nimport express from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { getDb } from './db.js';\nimport usersRouter from './routes/users.js';\nimport eventsRouter from './routes/events.js';\nimport queryRouter from './routes/query.js';\nimport dashboardsRouter from './routes/dashboards.js';\nimport exportRouter from './routes/export.js';\n\nexport function createApp(db?: Database.Database): express.Application {\n  const app = express();\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  const database = db ?? getDb();\n\n  app.use((req, _res, next) => {\n    (req as any).db = database;\n    next();\n  });\n\n  app.use('/api/users', usersRouter);\n  app.use('/api/events', eventsRouter);\n  app.use('/api/query', queryRouter);\n  app.use('/api/dashboards', dashboardsRouter);\n  app.use('/api/export', exportRouter);\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run full build and lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build && npm run lint\n```\nExpected: 0 errors, 0 warnings\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A\ngit commit -m \"feat: assemble final app with all routes\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Write Integration Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/tests/app.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 8\n\n**Step 1: Write tests covering all major features**\n\nCover: register, login, auth protection (401), event ingestion, batch, count query, timeseries, breakdown, dashboard CRUD, export JSON, export CSV, tenant isolation.\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/app.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../app.js';\nimport { getDb, resetDb } from '../db.js';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nlet db: Database.Database;\nlet app: ReturnType<typeof createApp>;\n\nbeforeEach(() => {\n  resetDb();\n  db = getDb(':memory:');\n  app = createApp(db);\n});\n\nafterEach(() => {\n  resetDb();\n});\n\nasync function registerAndLogin(email: string, tenantId: string, role = 'admin') {\n  const reg = await request(app)\n    .post('/api/users/register')\n    .send({ email, password: 'password123', tenantId, role });\n  return reg.body.token as string;\n}\n\ndescribe('User Management', () => {\n  it('registers a new user', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/users/register')\n      .send({ email: 'a@test.com', password: 'pass', tenantId: 'tenant1' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.token).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('returns 409 for duplicate email', async () => {\n    await request(app).post('/api/users/register').send({ email: 'a@test.com', password: 'p', tenantId: 't1' });\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/users/register').send({ email: 'a@test.com', password: 'p', tenantId: 't1' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(409);\n  });\n\n  it('logs in with correct credentials', async () => {\n    await request(app).post('/api/users/register').send({ email: 'b@test.com', password: 'pass', tenantId: 't1' });\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/users/login').send({ email: 'b@test.com', password: 'pass' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.token).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 for wrong password', async () => {\n    await request(app).post('/api/users/register').send({ email: 'c@test.com', password: 'pass', tenantId: 't1' });\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/users/login').send({ email: 'c@test.com', password: 'wrong' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 for unauthenticated /me', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/users/me');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n\n  it('returns user profile', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('d@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/users/me').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.email).toBe('d@test.com');\n  });\n\n  it('admin can change role of user in same tenant', async () => {\n    const adminToken = await registerAndLogin('admin@t.com', 'tenant1', 'admin');\n    const viewerReg = await request(app).post('/api/users/register')\n      .send({ email: 'viewer@t.com', password: 'pass', tenantId: 'tenant1', role: 'viewer' });\n    const viewerId = viewerReg.body.id;\n    const res = await request(app).patch(`/api/users/${viewerId}/role`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${adminToken}`)\n      .send({ role: 'editor' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.role).toBe('editor');\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Event Ingestion', () => {\n  it('ingests a single event', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('e@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/events')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' } });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.id).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 without auth', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/events').send({ name: 'test' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n\n  it('ingests batch events', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('f@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/events/batch')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ events: [{ name: 'click' }, { name: 'click' }, { name: 'view' }] });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.inserted).toBe(3);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Query Engine', () => {\n  async function setupData(token: string) {\n    await request(app).post('/api/events/batch')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ events: [\n        { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' } },\n        { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/about' } },\n        { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' } },\n        { name: 'click' },\n      ]});\n  }\n\n  it('counts events by name', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('g@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    await setupData(token);\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/query/count')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ eventName: 'page_view' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.count).toBe(3);\n  });\n\n  it('returns timeseries data', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('h@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    await setupData(token);\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/query/timeseries')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ eventName: 'page_view', interval: 'day' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(Array.isArray(res.body.data)).toBe(true);\n  });\n\n  it('returns breakdown data', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('i@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    await setupData(token);\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/query/breakdown')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ eventName: 'page_view', property: 'url' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.data.find((d: any) => d.value === '/home')?.count).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('enforces tenant isolation', async () => {\n    const t1 = await registerAndLogin('t1@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const t2 = await registerAndLogin('t2@test.com', 'tenant2');\n    await request(app).post('/api/events').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t1}`).send({ name: 'page_view' });\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/query/count')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t2}`)\n      .send({ eventName: 'page_view' });\n    expect(res.body.count).toBe(0);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Dashboard CRUD', () => {\n  it('creates a dashboard', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('j@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const res = await request(app).post('/api/dashboards')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'My Dashboard' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.id).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('lists dashboards for tenant', async () => {\n    const t1 = await registerAndLogin('k1@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const t2 = await registerAndLogin('k2@test.com', 'tenant2');\n    await request(app).post('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t1}`).send({ name: 'D1' });\n    await request(app).post('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t2}`).send({ name: 'D2' });\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t1}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(res.body[0].name).toBe('D1');\n  });\n\n  it('updates a dashboard', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('l@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const create = await request(app).post('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`).send({ name: 'Old' });\n    const res = await request(app).patch(`/api/dashboards/${create.body.id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'New' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.name).toBe('New');\n  });\n\n  it('deletes a dashboard', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('m@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const create = await request(app).post('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`).send({ name: 'Del' });\n    const res = await request(app).delete(`/api/dashboards/${create.body.id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(204);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Data Export', () => {\n  it('exports events as JSON', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('n@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    await request(app).post('/api/events').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`).send({ name: 'test' });\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/export/events').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(Array.isArray(res.body)).toBe(true);\n    expect(res.body[0].name).toBe('test');\n  });\n\n  it('exports events as CSV', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('o@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    await request(app).post('/api/events').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`).send({ name: 'test' });\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/export/events?format=csv').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.headers['content-type']).toContain('text/csv');\n    expect(res.text).toContain('id,tenant_id');\n  });\n\n  it('exports dashboard as JSON', async () => {\n    const token = await registerAndLogin('p@test.com', 'tenant1');\n    const dash = await request(app).post('/api/dashboards').set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`).send({ name: 'Exp' });\n    const res = await request(app).get(`/api/export/dashboards/${dash.body.id}`).set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.name).toBe('Exp');\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 for unauthenticated export', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app).get('/api/export/events');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\nExpected: all pass\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/tests/\ngit commit -m \"test: add integration tests for all API features\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Final Verification\n\n**Dependencies:** Tasks 1-9\n\n**Step 1: Full build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\nExpected: 0 errors\n\n**Step 2: Lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint\n```\nExpected: 0 errors\n\n**Step 3: Tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\nExpected: all pass\n\n**Step 4: Review diff**\n\n```bash\ngit diff HEAD~10\n```\n\n**Step 5: Final commit if needed**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"chore: analytics dashboard implementation complete\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- `bcryptjs` is not in package.json — use Node's built-in `crypto` for password hashing (scrypt or pbkdf2) OR check if `bcrypt` is available. Actually, use `crypto.scryptSync` from Node stdlib to avoid adding dependencies.\n- All routes that return tenant data must filter by `req.user!.tenant_id`\n- The `(req as any).db` pattern is necessary because Express's `Request` type doesn't have `db`; the `AuthRequest` interface solves this for authenticated routes\n- SQLite's `json_extract` function is used for property-based filtering in queries\n- The `resetDb()` function is critical for test isolation — call it in `afterEach`\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
